							<P>Whoa!&nbsp; Back in town finally..&nbsp; I flew in from Jacksonville tonight, and finally am just getting settled back in.&nbsp; I intended on deploying this next patch before I left, but it wasn`t fully tested by the time I had to leave, and I didn`t want to leave the service screwed up, especially since I couldnt fix it remotely.</P>
<P>I have the next patch pretty much finsished.&nbsp; I have to test it and resolve some minor quirks, but am 99% sure it will be ready tommorow.&nbsp; The patch will be the new custom roster, as well as support for FFXI, and Horizons guilds.</P>
<P>I will post a full patch description when I deploy it.. </P>
						</p>
					
						<hr />
					
						<h2>
							Edit Roster change
							Saturday, November 15, 2003 - 10:44:25 AM
						</h2>
						<p>
							<P>You don`t have to have all columns visable to admins to edit the roster anymore.&nbsp; I wrote a function that eliminates that need. </P>
<P>I wrote the function because I am kind shifting direction on my upcoming feature.&nbsp; I`ve decided to work on the Roster columns instead of the other things.&nbsp; Basically, this is going to allow you to add custom columns to the Roster.&nbsp; You will be able to add a column called "Date Joined", for example.&nbsp; So you will have the choice to use the standard Roster, or create your own custom Roster.&nbsp; When you create a custom Roster, you will have access to all the columns of the Standard Roster, just you can pick and choose your columns and add your own.</P>
<P>This might take a while to implement, so there might not be a patch for a week or so, depending how difficult this is going to be.</P>
						</p>
					
